#@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@
#***************************************************************************************
#*											*
#*    NEAT - an easy toolkit for biologists to analysis RNAseq/ChIPseq data		*
#*											*
#***************************************************************************************
#
#
# Follow the easy steps below to run NEAT
#---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# (1) 	Download the entire NEAT folder.
#	      Copy to any directory of your local computer.
#
#---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# (2)	In the RNAme/ChIPme folder, there are two applescripts
#
#     1. ChIPmE_1_Download
#     2. ChIPmE_2_Analysis
#
#     These are double clickable. Follow the steps.
#
#---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# (Notes for ChIPpip projects)	
#
#	(i)	  Ensure you Targets.txt file is properly filled out
#
#	(ii)	Ensure you have bed files of features of interest such as TSS, etc.
#       These can easily be created or requested (contact patrick.schorderet@molbio.mgh.harvard.edu)
#       They should be stored in the MartObjects directory
#
#---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# (Notes for RNApip projects)	
#
#	(i)	  Ensure you Targets.txt file is properly filled out
#
# (ii)  Create a folder named ReferenceFiles in the NEAT directory
#       Ensure you have dowloaded the appropriate .gtf file for your genome 
#       (check that it has the same name as in your Targets.txt file)
#       
# (iii) Ensure that the database (found in your Targets.txt file) you are attempting to use exists 
#
#---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
